  "description": "Variation of Condition 1 of planning permission dated 01 March 2018 (RN: 17/09342/FULL) as amended by a non material amendment dated 18 May 2020 (RN/20/03063) for, 'Demolition including the existing fourth floor, roof above and partial demolition of rear wall. External alterations including the erection of a replacement fourth floor with an additional single storey mansard storey at fifth floor level above; erection of an extension to the rear to new fifth floor level to provide an additional seven bedrooms for use in connection with the existing hotel (Class C1); extension to existing lift shaft with overrun and creation of new lift shaft with an overrun at new roof level; creation of a new green roof; relocation of existing roof plant within enclosures in two locations at fourth and fifth floor levels. reinstatement of Juliet balconies at first floor level and the erection of a new portico at ground floor level along the Clarges Street frontage. Internal alterations at all levels throughout and associated works (Site includes 39-42 Clarges Street)'; NAMELY, to allow the reconstruction of the rear wall of no. 7 Half Moon Street and the reconstruction and extension of the rear wall of no. 8 Half Moon Street; removal of a closet wing wall at the rear of no. 10 Half Moon Street  closest wing wall to facilitate a larger, more accessible lift lobby and associated removal of an adjacent window;  rebuilding and straightening of a corridor on the first and second floor of nos. 7 and 8 Half Moon Street; and associated works.",
